{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἐχθρός</b>, ά, όν, <br /> (ἔχθος) <b>hated, hateful</b>, of persons and things, frequently from [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus downwards (8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus has it only in this _passive_ sense)\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἐ. γάρ μοι κεῖνος ὁμῶς Ἀΐδαο πύλῃσι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 14.156, 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 9.312 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἐχθρὸν δέ μοί ἐστιν c.<i>infinitive</i>, 'tis <b>hateful</b> to me to.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 12.452; θεοῖσιν ἐ. 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Theogonia” 766, 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 601, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Equites” 34; ὁ θεοῖσιν ἐ. 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Comicus 74, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; compare θεοισεχθρός. <br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>active</i>, <b>hating, hostile</b>, first in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus and 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus (see. below 111), τινι 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 10.11, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Agesilaus” 6.1, etc.: with _genitive_, ὕβριος ἐχθρὰν ὁδόν\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] <b>averse from</b> insolence, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 7.90: _absolutely_, ἐ. γλῶσσα 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Choephori” 309 (_anapaest meter_); ὀργαί [prev. author] “Eu.” 937 (_anapaest meter_), etc.; ἀστέρες 2nd c.AD: Vettius Valens Astrologus 143.5. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> as <i>substantive</i>, ἐχθρός, ὁ, <b>enemy</b>, where the <i>active</i> and <i>passive</i> senses frequently coincide, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Opera et Dies” 342, 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 2.84, etc.; ἀνὴρ ἐ. 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.92; ὁ Διὸς ἐ. 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 120 (_anapaest meter_); ἐχθροῖς ἐχθρὰ πορσύνων [prev. author] “Ag.” 1374; εἴ.. τινα ἴδοι ἐχθρὸν ἑαυτοῦ 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.47; οἱ ἐμοὶ ἐ. [prev. author] 6.89, etc.—Acc. to 1st-2nd c.AD: Ammonius Grammaticus “περὶ ὁμοίων καὶ διαφόρων λέξεων” p.63 V., ἐχθρός\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] is <b>one who has been</b> φίλος, <b>but is alienated</b>; πολέμιος <b>one who is at war</b>; δυσμενής <b>one who has long been alienated and refuses to be reconciled.</b> <br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> regular <i>comparative</i> ἐχθρότερος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator “Prooemia” 40.3, “Anthologia Graeca” 5.160 (3rd c.BC: Hedylus Epigrammaticus or 3rd c.BC: Asclepiades Epigrammaticus)\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; <i>superlative</i> -ότατος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 1.65, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 1346 (Lyric poetry), 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 19.300: but more frequently irregular ἐχθίων, ἔχθιστος (which see). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__V</b></Level2> <i>adverb</i> ἐχθρῶς, μισοῦντες [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 697d, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>comparative</i> -οτέρως [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 5.18 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]: <i>superlative</i> -ότατα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 23.149. \">Refs</a>]","strongNumber":"G2190","accentedUnicode":"ἐχθρός","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G2189","matchingForm":"ἔχθρα","stepTransliteration":"echthra","gloss":"hostility","_zh_tw_Gloss":"仇敵, 冤仇","_es_Gloss":"hostilidad","_zh_Gloss":"仇敌, 冤仇"}],"shortDef":"(n.) enemy","mediumDef":"(n.) enemy <br /><b>hated, under disfavor,</b> <ref='Rom.11.28'>Rom. 11:28;</ref> <b>inimical, hostile,</b> <ref='Mat.13.28'>Mt. 13:28</ref>; <ref='Col.1.21'>Col. 1:21;</ref> as a <i>substantive</i>, <b>an enemy, adversary,</b> <ref='Mat.5.43, 44; 10:36'>Mt. 5:43, 44; 10:36</ref>; <ref='Luk.27.35'>Lk. 27:35</ref>","stepGloss":"enemy","stepTransliteration":"echthros","count":32,"_es_Definition":"enemigo  ; odiado","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 可恨的, 令人厭惡的, 可惡的<br>2) 敵對的, 仇恨的<br> 2a) 形容詞<br> 2b) 實名詞:敵人","_zh_Definition":"1) 可恨的, 令人厌恶的, 可恶的<br>2) 敌对的, 仇恨的<br> 2a) 形容词<br> 2b) 实名词:敌人","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"kẻ thù nghịch; một kẻ thù; ghét; kẻ địch; đối thủ. (Động từ ἔχθω: căm ghét, đối địch).","_zh_tw_Gloss":"仇敵","_es_Gloss":"enemigo","_zh_Gloss":"仇敌"}]}